<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="plone">

<body>

<tal:col metal:fill-slot="portlets_one_slot"></tal:col>
<tal:col metal:fill-slot="portlets_two_slot"></tal:col>

<metal:main fill-slot="main">
  <div id="indicator-container">

    <h1 id="parent-fieldname-title" class="documentFirstHeading">
      Nationally designated protected areas of Republic of Moldova
    </h1>

    <div class="documentDescription">
      Indicator assessment – known as D1. Protected areas – UNECE Environmental Indicators
    </div>

    <div id="content-core">
      <div id="themes-tags">
        <span class="listHead">Topics:</span>
        <span>
          <a class="link-category" rel="tag" href="https://www.eea.europa.eu/themes/biodiversity">
            Biodiversity — Ecosystems
          </a>
        </span>

        <span>
          <a class="link-category" rel="tag" href="https://www.eea.europa.eu/themes/agriculture">
            Agriculture
          </a>
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="keyMessage">
        <h3>Key messages</h3>
        <p>
In 2017, the share of protected areas is 6.4% of the total territory of the Republic of Moldova. Republic of Moldova is still far from reaching to national target of 10% of the country’s territory under the protected areas, neither Aichi target 11 of the Convention of Biological Diversity, which sets 17 % of terrestrial and inland water to be protected by 2020.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

